cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NA, cs.GR 

This paper deals with dimension reduction of SPD matrices used in image recognition, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm is based on manifold learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm involves constructing a Laplacian matrix, which is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper deals with the Lie group structure of SPD matrices, which is a topic in geometry and topology (cs.GR).
